{"title": "Damnation of Theron Ware", "description": "The Damnation of Theron Ware (published in England as Illumination) is an 1896 novel by American author Harold Frederic. It is widely considered a classic of American realism. The novel reveals a great deal about turn-of-the-century provincial America, religious life, and the depressed state of intellectual and artistic culture in small towns.<br /><br />\nThe novel centers on the life of a Methodist pastor named Theron Ware who has recently moved to a fictional small town in the Adirondack Mountains of upstate New York, which Frederic modeled after Utica, New York. A promising young pastor recently married, Theron has a number of experiences that cause him to begin to question the Methodist religion, his role as a priest and even the very existence of God. His moral decline (or illumination) is heightened through his dealings with Father Forbes, the town's Catholic priest; Dr. Ledsmar, a local atheist, philosopher, and man of science; and Celia, a local Irish Catholic girl, a species of aesthete, with whom Theron becomes hopelessly infatuated. (Introduction by Wikipedia)", "duration": 45791, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "892", "name": "Harold Frederic"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt27/Damnation_Theron_Ware_1301.jpg", "copyright_year": "1896", "genres": ["General Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Greg W."}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Greg W."}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mim@can (1949-2017)"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - Chapter 1", "readers": [4438], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/damnation_theronware_1005_librivox/thedamnationoftheronware_01_frederic_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1301}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - Chapter 2", "readers": [4438], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/damnation_theronware_1005_librivox/thedamnationoftheronware_02_